## Goal

Implement all tasks from the task list, in order, verifying each one before moving to the next.

## Steps

1. Load tasks: `memory_recall(topic_key="sdd-<change_id>-tasks")`
2. Load design: `memory_recall(topic_key="sdd-<change_id>-design")`
3. Load spec: `memory_recall(topic_key="sdd-<change_id>-spec")`
4. For each task:
   a. Implement the change in the specified files
   b. Run the project test suite — fix failures before moving on
   c. Verify the task's "Done when" condition is met
5. After all tasks complete, save implementation notes to memory:
   - title: `SDD Apply: <change_id>`
   - topic_key: `sdd-<change_id>-impl`
   - type: `context`
   - content: summary of what was changed, any deviations from the design, and test results

## Rules

- Do not add features beyond the task list — stay in scope
- Run tests after every task, not just at the end
- If a task conflicts with the design, note the deviation in the impl summary — do not silently deviate
- Keep commits atomic: one task per commit

## Board Update

**After saving implementation notes to memory**, update the project board. Check your prompt for an issue number (look for `for issue #N` or `#<number>`). If found, execute the commands below with `<ISSUE_NUMBER>` replaced by that number. **If no issue number is present in your prompt, skip this entire section.**

```bash
ITEM_ID=$(gh api graphql -f query='query{organization(login:"reverberage"){projectV2(number:2){items(first:100){nodes{id content{...on Issue{number}}}}}}}' --jq '.data.organization.projectV2.items.nodes[] | select(.content.number == <ISSUE_NUMBER>) | .id')
[ -n "$ITEM_ID" ] && gh project item-edit --id "$ITEM_ID" --field-id PVTSSF_lADOEeFGTc4Bc5CtzhXejII --project-id PVT_kwDOEeFGTc4Bc5Ct --single-select-option-id 47fc9ee4
[ -n "$ITEM_ID" ] && gh project item-edit --id "$ITEM_ID" --field-id PVTSSF_lADOEeFGTc4Bc5CtzhYUpaI --project-id PVT_kwDOEeFGTc4Bc5Ct --single-select-option-id e827dc3f
```
